A team led by Kabete MP Ferdinand Waititu (pictured) in the quest to wrest the Kiambu governor&rsquo;s seat from William Kabogo says it will address poverty and involve residents in decision-making.&ldquo;We want the people of Kiambu to make decisions on governance through public participation in line with the Constitution and this can only be done by kicking out the current administration,&rdquo; Waititu&rsquo;s running mate James Nyoro said in Gatundu on Sunday.